mini-gmp-plus provides CMake targets:

    find_package(mini-gmp-plus CONFIG REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE mini-gmp-plus::mini-gmp-plus)

The following headers are available:

    #include <mini-gmp-plus/mini-gmp.h>     // C interface for multiprecision integers
    #include <mini-gmp-plus/mini-mpq.h>     // C interface for multiprecision rationals
    #include <mini-gmp-plus/MiniMPZ.hpp>    // C++ wrapper class
    #include <mini-gmp-plus/bitops64.h>     // 64-bit operations helpers

Features:

  simd (default ON)
    SIMD-accelerated limb operations via xsimd (AVX2, SSE2, NEON).
    Enabled automatically when the 'simd' feature is selected (the default).

    To install without SIMD, add to your vcpkg.json:
        {
          "dependencies": [
            { "name": "mini-gmp-plus", "default-features": false }
          ]
        }

    To explicitly request SIMD:
        {
          "dependencies": [
            { "name": "mini-gmp-plus", "features": ["simd"] }
          ]
        }

